<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[175,1544,773,965]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis: This is a medium-sized (TL = 7-7.5), dull orange-brown species with long and slender legs and sue eyes in three diads. Legs and body thickly covered with two kinds of hairs; (1) long, suberect, denticulate hairs and (2) between them fine, procumbent, basally feathered hairs.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
