<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[228,1594,378,667]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Discussion: Violin spiders live on dark places on the ground or under bark, some species are cavemicolous. They do not make a real web by rather spin a few irregularly placed strands of silk that serve as retreats. Loxoscelids are notorious for their bites which may cause cutaneos necrosis, known as “necrotic arachnidism” or “loxoscelism”. Their venom is mainly cytotoxic and to a lesser extent also haemotoxic and neurotoxic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
